# =============================================================================
# For Testing on Physical Device with WiFi
# =============================================================================
# 1. Find your computer's local IP:
#    - macOS: System Settings > Network > WiFi Details > IP Address
#    - Windows: ipconfig (look for IPv4 Address)
#    - Linux: ifconfig or ip addr
#
# 2. Set EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL to your computer's IP:
#    Example: EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.100:3000/api
#
# 3. Make sure your phone and computer are on the same WiFi network
#
# 4. Restart the Expo app: npm start

# =============================================================================
# For Production Deployment
# =============================================================================
# 1. Deploy your server to a cloud provider:
#    - AWS EC2, DigitalOcean, Heroku, Railway, Render, etc.
#
# 2. Get your server's public URL:
#    Example: https://api.ksfashion.com
#
# 3. Update EXPO_PUBLIC_PROD_API_URL:
#    EXPO_PUBLIC_PROD_API_URL=https://api.ksfashion.com/api
#
# 4. Build production app:
#    eas build --platform ios
#    eas build --platform android

# =============================================================================
# Notes
# =============================================================================
# - Environment variables must start with EXPO_PUBLIC_ to be available in the app
# - Changes to .env require restarting the Metro bundler (npm start)
# - For physical devices on different networks (mobile data), use production URL
